Description:
    Generate a valid CustomCard::Configuration class.

    The resulting file is used when migrating an existing legacy Task to a new custom Card.

Syntax:
  rails generate custom_card:configuration "TITLE OF NEW CARD" [legacy task class name]

Example:
    rails generate custom_card "My New Cover Letter" TahiStandardTasks::CoverLetterTask

    This will create:
        lib/custom_card/configurations/my_new_cover_letter.rb

    Configuration file will contain the proper permissions from the legacy task.

Example (simple):
    rails generate custom_card:configuration "My First Cover Letter"

    This will create:
        lib/custom_card/configurations/my_first_cover_letter.rb

    Configuration file will assume that developer will manually set permissions.
